    {
      "id": "dc72af49949e590da81bbc56e094a0628961bbc2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2016-09-29 15:10:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThe following still returns a bunch of references:\n\n  git grep \"Please contact Sun Microsystems\"\n\nThere's also a couple of \"Please contact Oracle Corporation\" that could be removed (in another patch).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5edaa9044ab415d0475e5ada02dac69963044648",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-09-29 19:57:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(4 comments)\n\nLooks like the \"Please contact Sun\" messages are still in Makefile.in and autoMakefile.am, and a couple of scripts.\n\nAs with any patch this large, splitting it into a few separate parts decreases the chance of conflicts (e.g. I think you may even be conflicting with your own patch to remove the \"types.h\" file), and with \"Test-Parameters: trivial\" the testing shouldn't be an issue.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1fa87810bf8846ed7fca85d377c33d02a8bb0f2f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2016-09-30 16:16:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYeah my script to remove the \"Contact Sun\" was ignoring make files. As for conflicts I think we can avoid merge issues since this touches a spot few people ever change. Only problem is deletion which happens rarely. For my types.h deletion that file already has no Sun reference so its no problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
